1ï¸âƒ£ TextField

âœ… Definition

TextField is a high-level wrapper component that combines input, label, validation, and styling into a single form control.

Internally it uses:

FormControl

InputLabel

Input / OutlinedInput

FormHelperText



---

ğŸ” Core Concepts

1. Variants

outlined (default)

filled

standard


2. Controlled Component

const [name, setName] = React.useState("");

React controls the input value.


---

ğŸ’» Example

import { TextField } from "@mui/material";
import React from "react";

function Example() {
  const [email, setEmail] = React.useState("");

  return (
    <TextField
      label="Email"
      variant="outlined"
      fullWidth
      value={email}
      onChange={(e) => setEmail(e.target.value)}
      helperText="Enter your email"
    />
  );
}


---

2ï¸âƒ£ Select

âœ… Definition

Select is a dropdown component used to choose one or more options from a list.

It works with:

FormControl

InputLabel

MenuItem



---

ğŸ” Core Concepts

Single select vs multiple select

Controlled value

Label association for accessibility



---

ğŸ’» Example

import { FormControl, InputLabel, Select, MenuItem } from "@mui/material";
import React from "react";

function Example() {
  const [age, setAge] = React.useState("");

  return (
    <FormControl fullWidth>
      <InputLabel>Age</InputLabel>
      <Select
        value={age}
        label="Age"
        onChange={(e) => setAge(e.target.value)}
      >
        <MenuItem value={10}>Ten</MenuItem>
        <MenuItem value={20}>Twenty</MenuItem>
        <MenuItem value={30}>Thirty</MenuItem>
      </Select>
    </FormControl>
  );
}


---

3ï¸âƒ£ Checkbox

âœ… Definition

Checkbox allows users to select one or more options independently.

Used when:

Multiple selections allowed

True/false flags needed



---

ğŸ” Core Concepts

Boolean state

Controlled vs uncontrolled

FormControlLabel wrapper



---

ğŸ’» Example

import { Checkbox, FormControlLabel } from "@mui/material";
import React from "react";

function Example() {
  const [checked, setChecked] = React.useState(false);

  return (
    <FormControlLabel
      control={
        <Checkbox
          checked={checked}
          onChange={(e) => setChecked(e.target.checked)}
        />
      }
      label="Accept Terms"
    />
  );
}


---

4ï¸âƒ£ Radio

âœ… Definition

Radio buttons allow users to select exactly one option from a group.


---

ğŸ” Core Concepts

Must be used inside RadioGroup

Only one value selected

Controlled via value



---

ğŸ’» Example

import { Radio, RadioGroup, FormControlLabel } from "@mui/material";
import React from "react";

function Example() {
  const [gender, setGender] = React.useState("");

  return (
    <RadioGroup
      value={gender}
      onChange={(e) => setGender(e.target.value)}
    >
      <FormControlLabel value="male" control={<Radio />} label="Male" />
      <FormControlLabel value="female" control={<Radio />} label="Female" />
    </RadioGroup>
  );
}


---

5ï¸âƒ£ Switch

âœ… Definition

Switch is a toggle control used for turning a setting ON or OFF.

Visually different from checkbox â€” more modern toggle UI.


---

ğŸ’» Example

import { Switch, FormControlLabel } from "@mui/material";
import React from "react";

function Example() {
  const [darkMode, setDarkMode] = React.useState(false);

  return (
    <FormControlLabel
      control={
        <Switch
          checked={darkMode}
          onChange={(e) => setDarkMode(e.target.checked)}
        />
      }
      label="Dark Mode"
    />
  );
}


---

6ï¸âƒ£ Slider

âœ… Definition

Slider allows users to select a numeric value (or range) by dragging a thumb along a track.


---

ğŸ” Core Concepts

min / max values

step increments

marks (visual indicators)



---

ğŸ’» Example

import { Slider } from "@mui/material";
import React from "react";

function Example() {
  const [value, setValue] = React.useState(30);

  return (
    <Slider
      value={value}
      min={0}
      max={100}
      onChange={(e, newValue) => setValue(newValue)}
      valueLabelDisplay="auto"
    />
  );
}


---

7ï¸âƒ£ Autocomplete

âœ… Definition

Autocomplete is an advanced input that provides suggestions as the user types.

Used for:

Search fields

Country selectors

Tag systems



---

ğŸ’» Example

import { Autocomplete, TextField } from "@mui/material";

const countries = ["India", "USA", "Germany", "Japan"];

function Example() {
  return (
    <Autocomplete
      options={countries}
      renderInput={(params) => (
        <TextField {...params} label="Country" />
      )}
    />
  );
}


---

8ï¸âƒ£ Rating

âœ… Definition

Rating is a component used to collect user feedback through star-based scoring.

Common in:

Reviews

Product ratings

Feedback forms



---

ğŸ’» Example

import { Rating } from "@mui/material";
import React from "react";

function Example() {
  const [rating, setRating] = React.useState(3);

  return (
    <Rating
      value={rating}
      onChange={(event, newValue) => setRating(newValue)}
    />
  );
}


---

ğŸ§  Controlled vs Uncontrolled Concept

Most MUI inputs are controlled components:

value={state}
onChange={handler}

This gives:

Validation control

API integration

Predictable behavior

Form libraries support (Formik, React Hook Form)



---

ğŸ¯ Enterprise Usage Strategy

Component	Use Case

TextField	Login, forms
Select	Dropdown filters
Checkbox	Multi-select flags
Radio	Single choice
Switch	Settings toggle
Slider	Numeric range
Autocomplete	Search & suggestion
Rating	Feedback system



